This paper deals with formal grammars and parsing, which are topics commonly studied in programming languages (PL) and natural language processing (NLP) research. The use of parsing expressions and recognition-based semantics also suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and software engineering (SE) techniques. The paper also discusses language-preserving translations between different types of grammars, which falls under formal languages (FL) and computational linguistics (CL).
